		"description": "<p dir=\"ltr\">You have been taught to lead people in battle and the basics of strategy and tactics. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You have learned to keep your head in battle. If you fail a save against an effect that would cause you to become charmed, confused, or frightened, you can roll a d4 and add it to the result. Once you have used this benefit a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, you can&rsquo;t do so again until you finish a long rest.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You gain two Lessons of War from the marshal class. You must meet any prerequisites a given lesson has to select it.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>",
